; statnive.ir — NSD authoritative zone (Architecture C, Iranian-DC).
;
; Architecture C, dual-domain: statnive.ir = Iranian customers only.
; Origin: Asiatech AT-VPS-B1 (Tehran). Self-hosted NSD per the
; `iranian-dc-deploy` skill items 1+13 — no Cloudflare on the .ir
; chain (OFAC + sanctions surface). Single-primary, no AXFR-out;
; secondary nameserver inside Iran is a v1.1 item.
;
; This is a TEMPLATE — substitute the placeholders (in double-braces)
; below before loading into NSD via deploy/dns/at-vps-b1/install.sh.
;
;   {{ZONE_SERIAL}}           — YYYYMMDDNN; bump on every change
;   {{PRIMARY_NS_IPV4}}        — AT-VPS-B1 IPv4 (the box running NSD)
;   {{PRIMARY_NS_IPV6}}        — AT-VPS-B1 IPv6
;   {{ADMIN_EMAIL_DOTTED}}     — RFC 1035-encoded operator email
;                                (e.g. ops@statnive.ir → ops.statnive.ir.)
;   {{CUSTOMER_SLUG}}          — e.g. "sampleplatform"
;   {{CUSTOMER_VPS_IPV4}}      — Asiatech G2 IPv4 hosting the binary
;   {{CUSTOMER_VPS_IPV6}}      — Asiatech G2 IPv6 (empty if single-stack)
;
; CAA records lock cert issuance to letsencrypt.org + sectigo.com per
; iranian-dc-deploy item 12. Both are reachable from outside-Iran
; cert-forge boxes; Iranian-resident hosts MUST NOT issue ACME
; directly (iran-no-letsencrypt-in-binary).

$ORIGIN statnive.ir.
$TTL 300

; ===== SOA =====
@  3600  IN  SOA  ns1.statnive.ir. {{ADMIN_EMAIL_DOTTED}} (
            {{ZONE_SERIAL}}  ; serial — YYYYMMDDNN
            3600             ; refresh — secondary checks every 1h (v1.1)
            900              ; retry — back off 15m on failure
            604800           ; expire — secondary considers data stale after 7d
            300              ; minimum / negative-cache TTL
        )

; ===== NS — self-referential, single primary =====
@  3600  IN  NS  ns1.statnive.ir.

; ===== Primary NS glue =====
ns1     300  IN  A     {{PRIMARY_NS_IPV4}}
ns1     300  IN  AAAA  {{PRIMARY_NS_IPV6}}

; ===== Customer hostnames =====
; Each customer gets one subdomain pointing at their Asiatech VPS.
; Duplicate the CUSTOMER_SLUG / CUSTOMER_VPS_IPV4 / CUSTOMER_VPS_IPV6
; trio per customer; bump ZONE_SERIAL on every change.
{{CUSTOMER_SLUG}}      300  IN  A     {{CUSTOMER_VPS_IPV4}}
{{CUSTOMER_SLUG}}      300  IN  AAAA  {{CUSTOMER_VPS_IPV6}}

; ===== CAA records — cert issuance lock =====
; iranian-dc-deploy item 12: letsencrypt.org + sectigo.com (fallback
; ZeroSSL + Buypass tracked at the cert-forge level). issuewild=";"
; explicitly forbids wildcard certs — every subdomain gets its own
; PEM so a leak doesn't cascade across customers.
@  3600  IN  CAA  0 issue "letsencrypt.org"
@  3600  IN  CAA  0 issue "sectigo.com"
@  3600  IN  CAA  0 issuewild ";"
@  3600  IN  CAA  0 iodef "mailto:secops@statnive.ir"

; ===== Negative: explicit exclusions =====
; statnive.ir MUST NOT serve MX (no inbound email). support@statnive.com
; is the canonical mailbox per CLAUDE.md (statnive-fa / statnive-ar
; invariants). Operators must NOT add MX here without first updating
; that invariant in the parent CLAUDE.md.
;
; No SPF / DMARC needed for a zone that doesn't send mail.
